Endometriosis is a condition where bits of the uterus lining grow outside the uterus . 
  90 per cent of women will experience period pain . 
  Dr Lara Briden says severe pain can be a sign of more serious condition . 
  She says nausea, back or leg pain and bleeding between periods are signs . 
  Pain during or after sex can also be a warning sign . 
  Dr Briden gives her top tips for preventing period pain  . 
 